It was another tragic Monday in Enugu State as hoodlums enforcing Monday sit-at-home order launched an attack at holy ghost motor park leaving two people dead. Daily Independent learned that the hoodlums burnt Sienna bus during the attack. An eye witness account told our correspondent that the hoodlums who were masked came in a mini bus. He said “we were at the park waiting for early morning passengers when the gunmen arrived in a mini bus. “Immediately I saw them, i knew their mission was evil so I quickly left the park by the time I looked back I saw one of the Sienna bus in flames as gun shots rented the air. “We later learnt that two of the passengers were shot dead. When contacted, Enugu Police Public Relations Officer Daniel Ndukwe ASP did not reply the message to him In a related development, Car smashed by Tipper at Nza Street, Independence layout in Enugu metropolis on Monday morning POLL As usual, the roads were deserted due to sit at home. An eye witness account said that road which was deserted as  a result of the sit-at-home order couldn’t still contain the reckless lorry driver who was said to be on a high speed and smashed the car The accident left the car badly damaged while the Tipper ended up falling on its side saying no life was lost as people were not on the street due to sit at home.